---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { REPO_URL } from '../config';
---
<Base
  title="About"
  description="About Executor File and this site: what the tool is, who makes it, and how to get in touch."
>
  <div class="wrap prose">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Executor File is a free, open-source tool that gives your executor a
        map: an encrypted register of every account, asset and liability you
        own, and one printed page that says how to open it.
      </p>
      <p>
        It is made by <strong>Jamie Watters</strong>: 38 years in corporate
        technology, building open tools in public at{' '}
        <a href="https://jamiewatters.work">jamiewatters.work</a>. He built
        this after being the executor with nothing to go on;{' '}
        <a href="/story">the story is here</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Bugs, questions and ideas:</strong>
          <a href={`${REPO_URL}/issues`}>GitHub issues</a> is the canonical
          channel. Never paste real register contents, shares or passphrases
          into an issue.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Security reports:</strong> use GitHub's private vulnerability
          reporting, as described on <a href="/why-trust-this">Why trust this</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Support the work</h2>
      <p>
        The tool is free and stays free. If it has been useful and you feel
        like it, you can{' '}
        <a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/jamiewatters">buy Jamie a coffee</a>.
        No pressure either way; a mention to someone who needs it is worth as
        much.
      </p>
      <h2>This site</h2>
      <p>
        The site is static, open source in the same spirit as the tool, and
        built so that its technical claims are pulled from the tool's
        repository at build time rather than typed by hand.{' '}
        <a href="/money">How this site makes money</a> and{' '}
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a> cover the rest.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
